Pre-Game Insights: To finish off their tour of Australia, the West Indies will take on the host nation in three T20 internationals in February.
The Windies journey to Australia will be forever remembered for their first Test win in the region for 27 years in Brisbane.
Can the tourists cause problems for the green and gold in the shortest form of the game?
Miscellaneous Highlights: The first T20 match will be held at Blundstone Arena, Hobart on February 9, 2024, starting at 7:00pm AEDT.
The second T20 match will be held at Adelaide Oval, Adelaide on February 11, 2024, starting at 7:00pm AEDT / 6:30pm local.
The third T20 match will be held at Optus Stadium, Perth on February 13, 2024, starting at 7:00pm AEDT / 4:00pm local.
Every match of Australia's summer of cricket - including Tests, ODIs and T20Is - will be broadcast live on Fox Cricket and streamed on Kayo Sports.
Others: Australia's squad for the T20 series includes Mitch Marsh (c), Aaron Hardie, Sean Abbott, Marcus Stoinis, Jason Behrendorff, Glenn Maxwell, Tim David, Matthew Wade, Spencer Johnson, David Warner, Josh Inglis, and Adam Zampa.

West Indies' squad for the T20 series includes Rovman Powell (c), Kyle Mayers, Alzarri Joseph, Nicholas Pooran, Shai Hope, Andre Russell, Johnson Charles, Gudakesh Motie, Jason Holder, Sherfane Rutherford, Roston Chase, Romario Shepherd, Akeal Hosein, and Oshane Thomas.
